conbody.p: Create a single mline entity with multiple parallel lines and segments by specifying the start and endpoint of each segment. The mline is based on the current multiline style. Options allow you to specify the justification and scale.

section.title: Methods to create an mline
section.p: There are three methods to begin creating an mline:
You can continue adding unlimited segments until you press Enter to end the command.

Specify the endpoint of the mline segment.
Additional options: [Angle/Length/Follow/Close/Undo]
Begin creating an mline from the last point picked then:
Specify the endpoint of the mline segment.
Additional options: [Angle/Length/Follow/Close/Undo]
Begin creating an mline from the last drawn line segment, following its angle, then:
Specify the length of the mline segment. Picking a point only determines the length since the angle follows the previous segment.

section.title: Options within the MLINE command
section.p: After you begin creating an mline, the following options may be available:

dlentry.dd: Specify the justification of the mline relative to the start point.
The justification is saved in the CMLJUST variable.
Specify the overall scale of the mline.
The scale is saved in the CMLSCALE variable.
Specify the style to use for the mline as defined by the MLSTYLE command. The style is saved in the CMLSTYLE variable.
Additional option: [? to list available styles]
Type ? to view a list of all multiline styles that are defined in the drawing.
Specify the angle of the mline segment measured counterclockwise from the positive x-axis.
Specify the length of the mline segment.

Specify the angle of the mline segment measured counterclockwise from the positive x-axis.
Undo the last mline segment and continue drawing from its previous start point.
Automatically draw an mline segment from the end point of the last segment to the start point of the first segment.
